  "text": "In this paper, we examine the amplification and propagation of economic shocks, testing key features of financial accelerator models (e.g., [CITATION_1] , and Kiyotaki and Moore, 1997). In order to do so, we construct a novel database in the agricultural industry and use weather shocks as a source of exogenous productivity shocks. We then examine the relation between past weather shocks and farm productivity, land values, debt, and investment.",
